<br>
We have very set rules for when we do guild wars, and all my people follow those rules. <br>
<br>
We've had several wars and you can talk to any of the guilds we fought, we had very good times.<br>
<br>
Court of crosswinds tried to retake Halas from us, then we attacked Oggok and they defended.<br>
<br>
Crusaders reborn met us in Gfay and we fought them all night.<br>
<br>
PvP puts alot of excitment into the game, if you set the rules ahead of time.<br>
<br>
Out firm rules are<br>
<br>
War Rules<br>
<br>
- One Kill.. then move on, try to assist in res'ing or recovery <br>
- No Corpse camping<br>
- No Running or fleeing from battle(my guild only )<br>
- Keep Honor and dont turn down challenges regardless of level (my guild only)<br>
- Keep it In Character<br>
- And show some respect.. <br>
- No cross guild help, as in healing<br>
- Dont cause exp lose, as in no attacking while they fight a mob, attack right after <br>
- No public bitching in shouts or to others for die'ing, remember its all in fun.<br>
<br>
And then we add rules as other guilds ask, sometimes making safe spots, or other rules.<br>
<br>
You can not loot people on this server no matter what, and I think alot of people dont know that.<br>
<br>
So we look forward to anyone who wants to do something different over a weekend or a couple days. <br>
<br>
Wars can be as long or short as you would like to set, we just like the fun of stiring up the server.<br>
<br>
Yerig is our ambassador, send him a tell.<br>
<br>
We dont kill noobie guards to grief noobs btw. We only fight <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  inside</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> cities, where there is no real reason for guards anyways, and noobies can die.<br>
<br>
We kill those guards purly for RP, to inspire others to want to role play defending there city.<br>
<br>
Please learn about us before snapping at us.<br>
<br>
